cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with databases and their manipulation, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Database). The use of simplicial sets to represent the schema of a database suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as simplicial sets are a type of abstract mathematical structure. The use of polygons and paths in assembling and querying databases suggests a connection to cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of custom databases assembled from tiles suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning), as this is a common technique in deep learning. Finally, the use of queries and retrieval of records suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as this is a common task in AI applications.
